1.What is command-line Argument?
Ans) the agruments whic are passed on the terminal while running the script is known as CL-Arguments.

Important
=========
$? = exit code of the previous command execution
$@ = All the Agruments passed(space seperator)
$* = All the Arguments passed(single string)
$# = Number of arguments passed
$0 = script name
$1 = 1st argument
$2 = 2nd Argument
$3 = 3rd Argument
..
..
..
So On....etc
